user
Round 1 update. I addressed all four findings. Summary:

1. Long-poll subscribe: server.py now actually blocks via asyncio.sleep loop, polling the store until events appear or the configured timeout elapses. make_app gained subscribe_timeout + subscribe_poll_interval kwargs. StoreClient.subscribe accepts an optional timeout query param. Spec §6.2 contract now holds. Tests use short timeout (0.2s) to keep idle polls fast.

2. Success response codes: submit returns 200 + {}; integrate_trial returns 200 + {} (success + same-value idempotent); create_proposal and create_trial return 200 + the full entity (matching the entity schemas per §3 and §4).

3. Schema/model parity: claim-response.schema.json now rejects explicit null on expires_at (aligned with the NotNone discipline). Added tests/test_wire_schema_parity.py covering every wire model (request, response, events, error envelope) with accept + reject fixtures.

4. Tests rewritten:
   - TestIndeterminateIntegration now uses httpx.MockTransport with a handler that either (a) relays the request through a real TestClient to commit server-side before raising ConnectError on the original (confirmed-success branch), or (b) raises ConnectError without commit (indeterminate / divergence branches). No monkeypatching of StoreClient; no model_copy(update=...) on internal store state. The seed path uses _run_trial_to_success which drives the trial to success via the real Store API.
   - Added test_already_exists and test_conflicting_resubmission.
   - test_invalid_precondition now actually triggers InvalidPrecondition (integrate on a non-success trial), not IllegalTransition.
   - Added TestResponseCodes explicitly verifying 200s on submit/integrate and entity bodies on create_proposal/create_trial.

384 tests pass total (43 in eden-wire, up from 16). Ruff, pyright, markdownlint, spec-xref all clean.

Please re-review, focused on whether the four findings are actually resolved.

