     1	"""End-to-end round trip: StoreClient → FastAPI server → InMemoryStore.
     2	
     3	Every test here drives an in-process HTTP stack: FastAPI's TestClient
     4	wraps the ASGI app with an httpx-compatible transport so every request
     5	crosses the full serialization path without opening a real socket.
     6	StoreClient is constructed against that same TestClient so its
     7	request plumbing is identical to a subprocess-over-loopback run.
