1. Risk: `integrate_trial` still does not match the spec’s success body exactly. [server.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/src/eden_wire/server.py:443) now returns `200`, but it returns `{}`, which FastAPI serializes as a JSON body. [07-wire-protocol.md](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/spec/v0/07-wire-protocol.md:183) says the success response is `200, empty body`. So prior finding 2 is only partially resolved.

The other three findings look resolved on re-review. `/events/subscribe` now actually long-polls: [server.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/src/eden_wire/server.py:478) loops with `asyncio.sleep`, and a direct probe against the app showed an idle subscribe with `timeout=0.2` returning after about `0.223s`, not immediately. `create_proposal` and `create_trial` now return full entities ([server.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/src/eden_wire/server.py:320), [server.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/src/eden_wire/server.py:383)); the claim-response null drift is fixed in [claim-response.schema.json](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/spec/v0/schemas/wire/claim-response.schema.json:22) and covered by [test_wire_schema_parity.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/tests/test_wire_schema_parity.py:70); and the rewritten indeterminate-integration tests now use a real transport boundary instead of monkeypatching `StoreClient` ([test_wire_roundtrip.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/tests/test_wire_roundtrip.py:357), [test_wire_roundtrip.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-wire/tests/test_wire_roundtrip.py:406)).

